# CodeFlow Project Rules

## Positioning

**CodeFlow** (Chinese name: 码流) is a human-AI collaboration hub for multi-AI-role teams.

- **Phone**: Command center (ADMIN01) — send tasks, view status, scan to bind
- **PC**: Dedicated execution machine (CodeFlow Desktop) — receive tasks, write files, patrol, bridge
- **Relay**: Lightweight text event forwarding layer (`wss://your-relay-server/codeflow/ws/`)

## Naming

| Name | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| `CodeFlow` | Application-level name |
| `agent_bridge` | File collaboration protocol |
| `codeflow` | Python package / CLI (if present) |
| `ADMIN01` | Human operator |
| `PM01/DEV01/OPS01/QA01` | AI execution roles |

## Directory layout

```
BridgeFlow/
├── bridgeflow-nudger/   # PC Desktop (historical folder name; product: CodeFlow Desktop)
├── codeflow-plugin/     # Cursor MCP plugin
├── web/pwa/             # PWA source — sync to codeflow-pwa repo and bump version after changes
├── docs/
├── docs/agents/
├── server/relay/
└── scripts/
```

## Code standards

### Python
- Minimum: Python 3.10
- Package management: `pyproject.toml` (no `setup.py`)
- Cross-platform: Windows / macOS / Linux

### PWA (web/pwa/)
- Bump `config.js` `appVersion` on every change (Service Worker cache)
- Sync to `codeflow-pwa/` and push to GitHub Pages after changes
- Core features must not depend on CDN

### File protocol (agent_bridge)
- Task files: `TASK-YYYYMMDD-sequence-sender-to-recipient.md`
- YAML metadata header required on every file
- Do not relay content only in chat without saving to files

## Relay event shape

Outgoing events must include:
```json
{
  "room_key": "...",
  "sender": "ADMIN01",
  "client_type": "mobile_admin",
  "event_type": "...",
  "payload": {}
}
```

## Release

### PyPI
1. Bump `version` in `pyproject.toml`
2. Update `CHANGELOG.md`
3. Build: `py -3.10 -m build`
4. Upload: `py -3.10 -m twine upload dist/*`

### PWA (GitHub Pages)
1. Bump `appVersion` in `web/pwa/config.js`
2. Sync: `Copy-Item ..\web\pwa\index.html index.html -Force` (inside `codeflow-pwa/`)
3. Push: `git push origin main`

## Prohibited

- Do not hardcode real `room_key` in public examples
- Do not send large payloads over relay (8KB limit)
- Do not modify existing task files under `docs/agents/tasks/` and `reports/` (append only)
- Do not introduce a secondary chat-only protocol
